      "content": "That makes sense. So basically, if we follow that logic to its natural conclusion, any government agency trying to flag \"misinformation\" or \"harmful content\" is essentially just a state-run censorship bureau. Is it fair to say that from this perspective, there's no such thing as \"responsible\" regulation, only varying degrees of infringement?",
